{
  "text": "In this section we investigate the continuity of value function on initial surplus x. As in all \"exittype\" problem, the main subtle point here is that the ruin time \u03c4 \u03c0 , which obviously depend on the initial state x, is generally not continuous in x. We shall borrow the idea of penalty method (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] ), which we now describe.",
